All of these three important figure are very famous and very influential

139
00:11:52,820 --> 00:11:56,710
throughout the 20th century and 21st century.

140
00:11:56,710 --> 00:12:02,210
First one is Erving Goffman, sociologist.

141
00:12:02,210 --> 00:12:08,580
And he theorized the city as a performative place,

142
00:12:08,580 --> 00:12:13,830
or a kind of theater of gazing I already explained.

143
00:12:13,830 --> 00:12:19,980
Second, and maybe most important theorist is Michel Foucault.

144
00:12:19,980 --> 00:12:25,610
And Michel Foucault theorized and discussed

145
00:12:25,610 --> 00:12:31,910
the process of the production of self by the power of gazing.

146
00:12:31,910 --> 00:12:36,850
In his writing about prison or disciplinary power

147
00:12:36,850 --> 00:12:39,420
in contemporary society, or modern society

148
00:12:39,420 --> 00:12:45,370
is quite influential in many academic field.

149
00:12:45,370 --> 00:12:50,470
And finally third one is Marshall McLuhan.

150
00:12:50,470 --> 00:12:55,450
Marshall McLuhan emphasized the relationship media and message,

151
00:12:55,450 --> 00:12:59,090
and according his definition of media, we

152
00:12:59,090 --> 00:13:05,660
can expand the definition of the media in many, many different fields.

153
00:13:05,660 --> 00:13:10,440
Not only television, or a radio, or a photograph, and so on, but also

154
00:13:10,440 --> 00:13:14,680
the space, urban space itself including museum,

155
00:13:14,680 --> 00:13:17,780
or university can be defined as media.

156
00:13:17,780 --> 00:13:22,610


157
00:13:22,610 --> 00:13:29,560
I've been trying to integrate all of these three different perspectives

158
00:13:29,560 --> 00:13:32,640
in Tokyo, especially postwar Tokyo.

159
00:13:32,640 --> 00:13:35,220


160
00:13:35,220 --> 00:13:43,750
So from my perspective, on the one hand city's something like prison.

161
00:13:43,750 --> 00:13:47,320
The disciplinary power in Foucaltian sense

162
00:13:47,320 --> 00:13:51,360
are working and operating in the city.

163
00:13:51,360 --> 00:13:54,280
But at the same time city can be discussed

164
00:13:54,280 --> 00:13:56,470
as a theater in Goffman's sense.

165
00:13:56,470 --> 00:13:59,260


166
00:13:59,260 --> 00:14:05,500
And this city, city is prison, and the city is theater,

167
00:14:05,500 --> 00:14:12,230
but these cities are connected with many different type of media.

168
00:14:12,230 --> 00:14:19,830
Television, movie theater, and also media event and urban space,

169
00:14:19,830 --> 00:14:24,990
or some of the other media spaces.

